def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    # Handle hierarchical index columns
    index = data.index
    clevels = [index.levels[i] for i in clocs]
    ccodes = [index.codes[i] for i in clocs]
    cnames = [index.names[i] for i in clocs]

    # Handle remaining levels and create new MultiIndex
    rlevels = [index.levels[i] for i in range(index.nlevels) if i not in clocs]
    rcodes = [index.codes[i] for i in range(index.nlevels) if i not in clocs]
    rnames = [index.names[i] for i in range(index.nlevels) if i not in clocs]

    dummy_index = MultiIndex(
        levels=rlevels + [obs_ids],
        codes=rcodes + [comp_ids],
        names=rnames + ["__placeholder__"],
        verify_integrity=False,
    )

    # Create dummy DataFrame with new MultiIndex and unstack
    if isinstance(data, Series):
        dummy = data.copy()
        dummy.index = dummy_index
        unstacked = dummy.unstack("__placeholder__", fill_value=fill_value)
    else:
        dummy = data.copy()
        dummy.index = dummy_index
        unstacked = dummy.unstack("__placeholder__", fill_value=fill_value)

    # Set new columns and return unstacked DataFrame
    new_columns = MultiIndex(
        levels=clevels + [unstacked.columns.levels[0]],
        codes=ccodes + [unstacked.columns.codes[-1]],
        names=cnames + [unstacked.columns.name],
        verify_integrity=False
    )
    unstacked.columns = new_columns
    return unstacked
